NAME
    Mojolicious::Plugin::MediaQuery - Simulate media queries

VERSION
    0.01

DESCRIPTION
    This module allow you to embed a given web page inside an iframe, to see
    how it would look on different screens.

SYNOPSIS
    You need to enable the plugin in your Mojolicious application:

      use Mojolicious::Lite;
      plugin "MediaQuery";
      get "/" => sub { shift->render(text => "test\n") };
      app->start;

    The from the browser, you can ask for an URL with the "_mq" param to
    embed a website inside an iframe. Example:

      http://localhost:3000/some/path?_mq=iphone   # iphone portrait
      http://localhost:3000/some/path?_mq=r:iphone # iphone landscape
      http://localhost:3000/some/path?_mq=100x400  # width: 100px; height: 400px

ATTRIBUTES
  presets
    Defined presets:

      desktop: 992x
      ipad:    1024x768
      iphone:  320x480
      large:   1200x
      tablet:  768x

METHODS
  register
      $self->reqister($app, \%config);
      $app->plugin(MediaQuery => \%config);

    Will register an "around_dispatch" hook, which will trigger on the "_mq"
    query param. %config can contain:

    *   param

        Use this to specify another query param than the default "_mq".

    *   presets

        This should be a hash-ref with the same format as the attribute
        "presets".

AUTHOR
    Jan Henning Thorsen - "jhthorsen@cpan.org"

